nodes.id: Macro BIM Adoption- Comparative Market Analysis.pdf
nodes.label: Macro BIM Adoption- Comparative Market Analysis
nodes.desc: This paper is the second part of an ongoing Macro BIM Adoption study which clariﬁes how these models are validated through capturing the input of 99 experts from 21 countries using a survey tool; highlights the commonalities and diﬀerences between sample countries with respect to BIM adoption; and introduces sample tools and templates for either developing or calibrating BIM adoption policies.

nodes.id: The Five Components of BIM Performance Measurement.pdf
nodes.label: The Five Components of BIM Performance Measurement
nodes.desc: This paper identifies five complementary components specifically developed to enable such assessment : [1] BIM Capability Stages representing transformational milestones along the implementation continuum [2] BIM Maturity Levels representing the quality, predictability and variability within BIM Stages, [3] BIM Competencies representing incremental progressions towards and improvements within BIM Stages, [4] Organisational Scales representing the diversity of markets, disciplines and company sizes and [5] Granularity Levels enabling highly-targeted yet flexible performance analyses ranging from informal self-assessment to high-detail, formal organisational audits.

nodes.id: Lifecycle information transformation and exchange for delivering and managing digital and physical assets.pdf
nodes.label: LITE Framework
nodes.desc: A positioning paper introducing the Lifecycle Information Transformation and Exchange (LITE) framework, a conceptual structure for asset and project lifecycle information exchange and management.

nodes.label: Macro-BIM Adoption, Conceptual Structures
nodes.desc: This paper introduces a number of macro-adoption models, matrices and charts to systematically assess BIM adoption across markets, and inform the structured development of country-speciﬁc BIM adoption policies.

nodes.id: A competency knowledge-base for BIM learning.pdf
nodes.label: A Competency knowledge-base for BIM learning
nodes.desc: This paper introduces a conceptual workflow to identify, classify, and aggregate BIM competency items, acting as a knowledge-base for BIM learners and learning providers. It facilitates a common understanding of BIM deliverables and their requirements and supports national efforts to promote BIM learning.

nodes.id: An integrated approach to BIM competency assessment, acquisition and application.pdf
nodes.label: BIM Competency Assessment
nodes.desc: Discusses an integrated approach to BIM competency assessment, acquisition, and application, focusing on individual BIM competencies and their role in organizational capability.

nodes.label: BIM Maturity Matrix
nodes.desc: A document detailing a BIM maturity matrix for assessing BIM capability, maturity, and performance improvement.

nodes.label: Model Uses: Foundations for a Modular Requirements Clarification Language
nodes.desc: This paper introduces the Model Uses concept, comprising a Model Uses Taxonomy and a Model Uses List, explores the conceptual foundations of Model Uses and then provides practical examples – an implementation task list and an assessment module - of how this modular language assists in identifying BIM project requirements and facilitating project delivery.

nodes.id: Building Information Modelling- conceptual constructs and performance improvement tools.pdf
nodes.label: Building Information Modelling- conceptual constructs and performance improvement tools.pdf
nodes.desc: This document is a PhD thesis by Bilal Succar focusing on conceptual constructs and performance improvement tools in BIM.

nodes.label: Building Information Modelling: Point of Adoption
nodes.desc: This paper introduces the Point of Adoption (PoA) model which integrates concepts of BIM readiness, implementation, and diffusion into a single visual model to assess organizational abilities and clarify a step-wise approach to BIM adoption and continuous performance improvement.

nodes.label: BIM Education, BIM in Practice
nodes.desc: A collection of three documents from the BIM Education Working Group (EWG) of the Australian Institute of Architects and Consult Australia.  It covers BIM Education, BIM Learners, BIM Learning Providers, and the BIM Learning Spectrum.

nodes.id: Towards a taxonomy of built asset lifecycle information coupling.pdf
nodes.label: Towards a taxonomy of built asset lifecycle information coupling
nodes.desc: This paper proposes a taxonomy of Built Asset Lifecycle Information Couples which provides the core elements, definitions and characteristics framing the physical-digital coupling of assets and resources in the built asset industry.

nodes.id: A proposed approach to comparing the BIM maturity of countries.pdf
nodes.label: A proposed approach to comparing the BIM maturity of countries
nodes.desc: This paper proposes three metrics to augment survey data and help establish the overall BIM maturity of countries. These metrics apply to noteworthy BIM publications (NBP)s and assess their BIM knowledge content (BKC).

nodes.id: Building Information Modelling Framework- a Research and Delivery Foundation for Industry Stakeholders.pdf
nodes.label: BIM Framework Paper
nodes.desc: A research paper introducing the BIM Framework, a foundation for industry stakeholders, exploring concepts, stages, steps, and lenses, and employing visual knowledge models and a specialized ontology.

nodes.label: Measuring BIM Performance
nodes.desc: This article identifies five complementary components developed to enable BIM performance assessment: (i) BIM capability stages; (ii) BIM maturity levels; (iii) BIM competencies; (iv) Organizational Scales; and (v) Granularity Levels.

nodes.id: Building Information Modeling Analyzing Noteworthy Publications of Eight Countries Using a Knowledge Content Taxonomy.pdf
nodes.label: BIM Analyzing Publications
nodes.desc: Analysis of noteworthy BIM publications from eight countries using a knowledge content taxonomy.

nodes.id: A Proposed Framework To Investigate Building Information Modelling Through Knowledge Elicitation And Visual Models.pdf
nodes.label: BIM Framework Paper
nodes.desc: This paper introduces a research framework for identifying BIM concepts and a methodology for capturing and representing BIM interactions. It also proposes visual models to elicit expert knowledge and identifies further research requirements.
